00:14:41.780 --> 00:14:44.000
A couple of things just kind of technically speaking

00:14:44.000 --> 00:14:46.140
that are worth noting is one,

00:14:46.140 --> 00:14:47.419
Amazon automatically,

00:14:47.419 --> 00:14:50.179
so SageMaker automatically mounts a home directory

00:14:50.179 --> 00:14:51.780
into every session.

00:14:51.780 --> 00:14:53.619
So you'll see down here in the bottom right-hand corner

00:14:53.619 --> 00:14:54.859
when I look at files,

00:14:54.859 --> 00:14:56.859
I have a home directory available to me

00:14:56.859 --> 00:14:59.719
inside this home direct, this home directory is persistent.

00:14:59.719 --> 00:15:01.099
So this is nice because this means

00:15:01.099 --> 00:15:04.479
that if I am working on a project and I,

00:15:04.479 --> 00:15:07.340
let's say that I start a project in SageMaker

00:15:07.340 --> 00:15:09.179
and I realized part of the way through

00:15:09.179 --> 00:15:11.280
that I've under provisioned my environment,

00:15:11.280 --> 00:15:13.219
I didn't give myself enough resources.

00:15:13.219 --> 00:15:15.700
And if I want to be able to conclude my analysis,

00:15:15.700 --> 00:15:20.700
I need to do it in a more heavily provisioned environment.

00:15:20.700 --> 00:15:22.539
Well, I can terminate my existing session.

00:15:22.539 --> 00:15:24.260
I can save my changes, first of all,

00:15:24.260 --> 00:15:25.739
terminate my existing session,

00:15:25.739 --> 00:15:28.640
start a new session with a new, bigger environment

00:15:28.640 --> 00:15:31.539
based on what I've learned from the previous session.

00:15:31.539 --> 00:15:33.580
And then once that environment starts up,

00:15:33.580 --> 00:15:35.659
I'll have access back to the same files

00:15:35.659 --> 00:15:38.320
I was working on previously within my home directory.

00:15:38.320 --> 00:15:40.280
So these files follow you around.

00:15:40.280 --> 00:15:41.780
This also means by extension

00:15:41.780 --> 00:15:44.500
that if I install an R package, right?

00:15:44.500 --> 00:15:47.979
If I'm in here and I say install packages,

00:15:49.419 --> 00:15:53.179
let's do, yeah, let's install the line package.

00:15:53.179 --> 00:15:55.580
Then this package will install into my home directory

00:15:55.580 --> 00:15:57.500
as a user package.

00:15:57.500 --> 00:15:59.659
And then it will be available to me

00:15:59.659 --> 00:16:01.140
persistently from that point forward.

00:16:01.140 --> 00:16:02.780
So I don't need to reinstall packages

00:16:02.780 --> 00:16:04.960
every time I start a new session in SageMaker.

00:16:04.960 --> 00:16:06.700
Those packages are persistent

00:16:06.700 --> 00:16:08.859
and follow me into whatever session

00:16:08.859 --> 00:16:10.700
I happen to be running on.

00:16:10.700 --> 00:16:12.739
And we can see those packages installed.

00:16:12.739 --> 00:16:14.340
