00:45:27.620 --> 00:45:30.780
do you need a paid RStudio Workbench license

00:45:30.780 --> 00:45:33.580
in order to use RStudio in SageMaker?

00:45:34.580 --> 00:45:38.580
Yes, the way that we've shown this integration today,

00:45:38.580 --> 00:45:41.379
it only works with a paid RStudio Workbench license.

00:45:43.139 --> 00:45:44.340
And that can be just to elaborate

00:45:44.340 --> 00:45:45.580
on that a little bit further,

00:45:45.580 --> 00:45:46.860
that can be either standard,

00:45:46.860 --> 00:45:49.820
which is a license for one server, one activation

00:45:49.820 --> 00:45:53.020
or enterprise, which gives you unlimited server activations.

00:45:53.020 --> 00:45:55.260
Both of those models will work with SageMaker.

00:45:55.739 --> 00:45:56.580
If you do standard,

00:45:56.580 --> 00:45:58.939
then SageMaker becomes your one installation of RStudio.

00:45:58.939 --> 00:46:00.219
If you have enterprise,

00:46:00.219 --> 00:46:02.219
you could be running RStudio in SageMaker

00:46:02.219 --> 00:46:04.419
as well as have your own on-prem solution.

00:46:04.419 --> 00:46:06.780
You can, you have lots of flexibility at that point.

00:46:06.780 --> 00:46:08.780
But the answer to that question is yes,

00:46:08.780 --> 00:46:11.699
it does require a license for RStudio Workbench.

