00:46:54.580 --> 00:46:55.419
I'm happy to be corrected by the folks

00:46:55.419 --> 00:46:56.540
on the Amazon side as well.

00:46:56.540 --> 00:46:59.860
But from my understanding today, right?

00:47:01.459 --> 00:47:04.179
Most of the functionality when you interact directly

00:47:04.179 --> 00:47:06.020
with SageMaker is going to come through

00:47:06.020 --> 00:47:07.699
that SageMaker Python SDK.

00:47:07.699 --> 00:47:10.219
So like we use reticulate, we brought that module in

00:47:10.219 --> 00:47:12.580
and then we use methods and functions from that module

00:47:12.580 --> 00:47:15.219
to manipulate and train a model and deploy the model

00:47:15.219 --> 00:47:16.939
and all those types of things.

00:47:16.939 --> 00:47:20.500
Now, one of the kind of underlying components of that

00:47:20.500 --> 00:47:22.500
is the fact that all that whole process,

00:47:22.500 --> 00:47:24.300
that model training, tuning, deployment process

00:47:25.060 --> 00:47:26.260
is all actually happening in Python, right?

00:47:26.260 --> 00:47:28.780
The container that we ran was running XGBoost

00:47:28.780 --> 00:47:30.979
