00:47:30.979 --> 00:47:32.979
We were managing it from the R side with reticulate,

00:47:32.979 --> 00:47:35.780
but most of the work was being done on the Python side.

00:47:35.780 --> 00:47:37.739
Now, there is support in SageMaker

00:47:37.739 --> 00:47:40.820
for being able to define kind of your own custom containers

00:47:40.820 --> 00:47:42.620
and images for model training and deployment

00:47:42.620 --> 00:47:46.419
where you could define ways to interact with R processes.

00:47:46.419 --> 00:47:47.699
But to my understanding today,

00:47:47.699 --> 00:47:50.459
there's not a lot of native R tooling there yet.

00:47:50.459 --> 00:47:52.620
Now, that's something I'd love to see change

00:47:52.659 --> 00:47:54.699
and something that I'm hopeful will change over time

00:47:54.699 --> 00:47:57.860
as this partnership continues to grow and expand.

00:47:57.860 --> 00:47:58.979
I've had discussions with folks

00:47:58.979 --> 00:48:01.340
about some changes I'd like to see, for example,

00:48:01.340 --> 00:48:03.780
and this isn't an indication that this will happen,

00:48:03.780 --> 00:48:07.500
but my own personal just utopian future

00:48:07.500 --> 00:48:10.300
would be that there is an R native SDK for SageMaker

00:48:10.300 --> 00:48:12.179
that allows R users to natively interact

00:48:12.179 --> 00:48:13.219
with SageMaker resources,

00:48:13.219 --> 00:48:15.860
as well as support for things like tidy models

00:48:15.860 --> 00:48:16.860
and SageMaker.

00:48:16.860 --> 00:48:19.139
Now, there's a lot of work to be done to get there.

00:48:19.139 --> 00:48:20.419
And again, this isn't a promise

00:48:20.419 --> 00:48:21.939
that that will ever come to fruition,

00:48:22.260 --> 00:48:24.379
but it's something that I'd like to work towards

00:48:24.379 --> 00:48:25.820
and would love to see happen.

00:48:29.060 --> 00:48:29.899
And today-

00:48:29.899 --> 00:48:30.739
This is Michael.

00:48:30.739 --> 00:48:35.100
So I'd like to add on what James has provided.

00:48:35.100 --> 00:48:39.060
In SageMaker, you can definitely bring in your R containers.

00:48:39.060 --> 00:48:41.139
So you can package your tidy models,

00:48:41.139 --> 00:48:44.300
correct into a container and start a training

00:48:44.300 --> 00:48:48.540
and also hosting your models built natively within R

00:48:48.540 --> 00:48:50.020
into SageMaker.

00:48:50.060 --> 00:48:54.500
And then, you know, and doing all the ML Ops CLCD

00:48:54.500 --> 00:48:57.739
along with SageMaker using the SageMaker SDK

00:48:57.739 --> 00:48:59.139
within your R environment.

00:48:59.139 --> 00:49:03.060
So we do have a couple of resources and artifacts

00:49:03.060 --> 00:49:04.139
showing how to do so.

00:49:04.139 --> 00:49:06.139
So happy to share those information.

00:49:08.179 --> 00:49:09.580
Awesome. Thank you, Michael.

00:49:10.419 --> 00:49:13.379
And James, I know you addressed this question

00:49:13.379 --> 00:49:14.379
a bit towards the end,

00:49:14.379 --> 00:49:16.100
but I think it'd be good to address as well.

00:49:16.100 --> 00:49:18.100
But Sheikha asks,

00:49:18.100 --> 00:49:19.899
is it a good solution for host-

00:49:19.899 --> 00:49:21.379
Is this a good solution for hosting

00:49:21.379 --> 00:49:23.540
and developing Shiny applications?

00:49:24.580 --> 00:49:27.979
Yeah. So for developing, absolutely, right?

00:49:27.979 --> 00:49:29.500
It gives you a valid environment

00:49:29.500 --> 00:49:31.500
where you can develop these Shiny applications.

00:49:31.500 --> 00:49:34.219
And the nice thing is you can develop these applications

00:49:34.219 --> 00:49:35.780
in a way that natively reaches out to

00:49:35.780 --> 00:49:37.500
and interacts with your AWS resources.

00:49:37.500 --> 00:49:38.899
So it becomes really easy

00:49:38.899 --> 00:49:41.699
because you're already operating inside of AWS

00:49:41.699 --> 00:49:43.179
to read data in from S3

00:49:43.179 --> 00:49:44.979
and to interact with other AWS resources

00:49:44.979 --> 00:49:47.659
without needing to worry about like credential management.

00:49:47.659 --> 00:49:49.659
Now that's on the development side.

00:49:49.659 --> 00:49:51.580
On the like publication and hosting side,

00:49:51.580 --> 00:49:52.860
this story is a little bit different today

00:49:52.860 --> 00:49:55.459
because currently RStudio Connect,

00:49:55.459 --> 00:49:56.860
which would be kind of the preferred method

00:49:56.860 --> 00:49:59.699
of deploying and hosting Shiny applications,

00:49:59.699 --> 00:50:01.860
isn't something that's offered through SageMaker.

00:50:01.860 --> 00:50:05.139
That's the next step for us is making that available.

00:50:05.139 --> 00:50:07.659
And it's something that's under current conversation

00:50:07.659 --> 00:50:09.179
to have done.

00:50:09.179 --> 00:50:12.459
And so we're hopeful that that will be available shortly.

00:50:12.459 --> 00:50:13.580
But in the meantime,

00:50:13.580 --> 00:50:14.979
what that means is you would develop

00:50:14.979 --> 00:50:17.620
inside of RStudio Workbench on SageMaker

00:50:18.459 --> 00:50:20.060
and then you would publish or deploy that application

00:50:20.060 --> 00:50:21.060
to some other location,

00:50:21.060 --> 00:50:22.659
whether that's RStudio Connect

00:50:22.659 --> 00:50:24.100
that you have separately installed

00:50:24.100 --> 00:50:25.419
and managed somewhere else,

00:50:25.419 --> 00:50:28.780
or Shiny Apps IO or some other solution.

00:50:28.780 --> 00:50:30.340
The challenge with that is the fact that

00:50:30.340 --> 00:50:32.060
once you kind of cross that boundary

00:50:32.060 --> 00:50:33.219
and you're no longer operating

00:50:33.219 --> 00:50:35.379
inside of that kind of SageMaker domain,

00:50:35.379 --> 00:50:36.739
now you have to start thinking about like,

00:50:36.739 --> 00:50:37.580
how do I, you know,

00:50:37.580 --> 00:50:39.739
if I'm interacting with other AWS services,

00:50:39.739 --> 00:50:41.060
for example, like S3,

00:50:41.060 --> 00:50:42.820
now I need to make sure that I have my credentials

00:50:42.820 --> 00:50:44.300
under control and I know what I'm doing

00:50:44.300 --> 00:50:47.260
in terms of like authenticating to the service.

00:50:47.659 --> 00:50:51.300
When RStudio Connect becomes available through SageMaker,

00:50:51.300 --> 00:50:52.300
I imagine that that story

00:50:52.300 --> 00:50:53.459
will become a little bit more clear

00:50:53.459 --> 00:50:55.179
because you'll be able to publish directly

00:50:55.179 --> 00:50:58.100
from Workbench on SageMaker to Connect on SageMaker

00:50:58.100 --> 00:50:59.860
and you'll still have that same kind of

00:50:59.860 --> 00:51:02.580
nice native authentication that's already taken place.

00:51:05.659 --> 00:51:06.699
Awesome, thank you.

